### 11. **LogService fix - PASS**

**Location:** `/home/someone/Documents/eagle-point/w2t50/repo/app/service/LogService.php` line 67

**Finding:** There IS an is_string($key) check before strtolower():

```php
private static function maskSensitive(array $data): array
{
    foreach ($data as $key => $value) {
        if (is_array($value)) {
            $data[$key] = self::maskSensitive($value);
        } elseif (is_string($key) && in_array(strtolower($key), self::$sensitiveKeys, true)) {
            $data[$key] = '[REDACTED]';
        }
    }
    return $data;
}
```

Line 67 explicitly checks: `is_string($key) &&` before calling `strtolower($key)`. This prevents errors if array keys are integers.

**Verdict:** CORRECT - Defensive programming in place to prevent strtolower() on non-string keys.

